folder: Arthur Kill Road & Arden Avenue, Staten Island, NY
original_title: Richmond: Arthur Kill Road - Arden Avenue
text:
Arthur Kill Road, north side, east of Arden Ave., Showing the J. Mills house. The house is about 660 yards back of the road near
Benedicts Creek.
April 9, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.

folder: Arthur Kill Road & Arden Avenue, Staten Island, NY
original_title: Richmond: Arthur Kill Road - Arden Avenue
text:
1765 and 1767 Arthur Kill Road, north side, adjoining the N.E. corner of Arden Avenue, showing tenements that belonged to The Rossville Brick Company whose factory was located directly in back of the houses. The view is southward toward Arden Avenue.
May 5, 1929
P. L. Sperr

folder: Arthur Kill Road & Arden Avenue, Staten Island, NY
original_title: Richmond: Arthur Kill Road - Arden Avenue
text:
Arthur Kill Road (foreground), north side, east of Arden Avenue (beside No. 1765). This lane runs north from Arthur Kill Road for about 800 yards and is the driveway to the Rossville Brick Company factory.

May 5, 1929

P.L. Sperr
